<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4773725>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 4. Discosauriscus pulcherrimus (FRITSCH, 1880), G 151. a: detail of the postcranial skeleton, b: left humerus, ulna and radius,c: right metacarpals,radius and ulna,d: pectoral girdle, e: hind limb elements, f: posteriormost presacral andsacral portion of the axial skeleton, g: imprints of scales in the posterior presacral region. Abbreviations: CL – clavicle, CTH – cleithrum, ect. – ectepicondyle, ent. – entepicondyle, ent.f. – entepicondyle foramen, FE – femur, FI – fibula, HU – humerus, ICL – interclavicle, im. of sc. – imprints of scales, met. – metacarpals, PC – pleurocentrum, sg.b. – supraglenoid buttress, R – ribs, RA – radius, RA+UL – radius and ulna, SC – scapula, TI – tibia, UL – ulna." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4773725/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4773719>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 3. Discosauriscus pulcherrimus (FRITSCH, 1880), G 151. a–h: 3D virtual models of the selected dermal cranial bones; a, b: right tabular in dorsal (a) and ventral (b) views, c, d: right postparietal in dorsal (c) and ventral (d) views, e, f: right postorbital in dorsal (e) and ventral (f) views, g, h: left jugal in dorsal (g) and ventral (h) views. Abbreviations: cr. arc. – arcuate crest, oc. fl. – occipital flange, pr. tab. – tabular process, tr. rid. – transverse ridge." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4773719/files/figure.png" .

